      "id": "LN_01",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "What Are Equal Groups?",
      "content": "Equal groups all have the SAME number of objects. 3 plates with 4 cookies each = 3 equal groups of 4. If one plate has 5 cookies and the others have 4, the groups are NOT equal.",
      "cpa_phase": "concrete",
      "visual_type": "manipulative",
      "visual_data": {"tool": "array_grid", "config": {"rows": 3, "cols": 4}}
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_02",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Skip Counting to Find the Total",
      "content": "Skip count by the number in each group. For 4 groups of 5: count 5, 10, 15, 20. That's the total — 20 in all.",
      "cpa_phase": "concrete",
      "visual_type": "manipulative",
      "visual_data": {"tool": "array_grid", "config": {"rows": 4, "cols": 5}}
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_03",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Groups Of",
      "content": "'3 groups of 6' means 3 groups, each with 6 objects. Total = 6 + 6 + 6 = 18. This is the same as 3 × 6 = 18.",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "manipulative",
      "visual_data": {"tool": "array_grid", "config": {"rows": 3, "cols": 6}}
