    {
      "id": "LN_04",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Repeated Addition",
      "content": "Equal groups are the same as adding the same number over and over. 5 groups of 3 = 3 + 3 + 3 + 3 + 3 = 15. This idea is the start of multiplication.",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "none"
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_05",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Reading Problems Carefully",
      "content": "Look for words like 'each', 'every', 'per' — they tell you equal groups. 'Each box has 4 pencils, 5 boxes' → 5 groups of 4, not 4 groups of 5. The number of GROUPS is 5; the SIZE of each group is 4.",
